{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1a0f361-1dd7-4e63-8dad-1da5b4542f55","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit (v2)**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit (v3)**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]          // same as v2\n[Fact(Explicit = true)]                       // runs only when explicitly requested\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nAll frameworks require a reason string. Skipped tests appear in results as \"skipped\" / \"ignored\" rather than passed or failed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ad2a139-4bb8-48ee-a9fa-e417317defe9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"A028:E52A2:183C106:1B855DB:69FE8A1E"},"id":"cef96faf-80d7-4dca-b481-11572a294aeb","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:13:10.098Z","parentId":"47d7a782-6977-42b7-b2d3-511312aabb45"}
